  <front>
   <head>THE DIRGE OF AMORET.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHY glide the hours so swift away,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">When love and fortune shine?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Years seem'd but as a passing day,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">When Amoret was mine.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Was mine! sad sounds, ye ring my knell,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And bid to joy a long farewell!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her voice could sooth the soul of care,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And lull despair to rest;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why was she form'd divinely fair?</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And why was I so bless'd?</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So bless'd no more; I hear the knell,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which bids the world a long farewell.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
